    <text>
        <body>
            <div style="handwritten" type="letter">
                <head type="title">Miklós Oláh to Johan Weze (Brussels, 4 March 1534)</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p>It has been decided that Christina of Denmark will move to Milan on the
                                10<hi rend="super">th</hi> of this month, and Jacobus a Flandria
                            will accompany her. He is expecting Weze’s letter on Lodovico
                            Gritti.</p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb/>
                <p>Nicolai Olai ad Ioannem archiepiscopum Lundensem oratorem caesaris. </p>
                <p>Brevior nunc sum, quia non est aliquid, de quo scribam. Omnem seriem
                    rerum tuarum iampridem ex meis litteris<note type="critic">See Ep. 449. and Ep.
                        455.</note><ref>/o:olahus.tei.15340208_1</ref><ref>/o:olahus.tei.15340217_1</ref>
                    accepisti. Constitutum hic est, ut princeps
                        <persName>Christierna</persName><note type="critic">Christina of Denmark
                        married Francesco II Sforza, Duke of Milan on 23 September, 1533.</note>
                    decimo huius mensis die hinc se moveat <placeName>Mediolanum</placeName>.
                        <persName>Dominus a Prato</persName><note type="critic">Jacobus a
                        Flandria.</note> eam conducet, habebit honorificam familiam et bonum
                    apparatum. Mitto cum praesentibus litteras <persName>Stanshardi</persName>.<note
                        type="critic">We do not know him more closely, see Ep. 375. Note
                        10.</note><ref>/o:olahus.tei.15330605_4</ref> Arbitror
                        <persName>Cornelium</persName><note type="critic">Cornelis de
                        Schepper.</note> in curia non esse, propterea ad eum non scribo. Exspecto
                    litteras tuas de <persName>Grito</persName><note type="critic">Lodovico
                        Gritti.</note> aliisque rebus. Vale feliciter. </p>
                <p><placeName>Bruxellae</placeName> 4. Martii 1534.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
